---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import Vera from "../components/Vera.astro";
import VeraTree from "../components/VeraTree.astro";
---

<Layout>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-24 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="font-['Raleway'] text-8xl text-gray-600 font-bold">The Power of Big Data...</h1>
      <br><br>
      <h2 class="text-6xl font-bold text-center text-gray-900 mb-8">Now Available in All Sizes!</h2>
      <br>
      <div class="flex justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="individuals" class="px-8 py-3 bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 text-lg rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-300 transition">For Individuals</a>
        <a href="teams" class="px-8 py-3 bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 text-lg rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-300 transition">For Teams</a>
        <a href="leaders" class="px-8 py-3 bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 text-lg rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-300 transition">For Leaders</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

<section class="bg-white py-24">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div class="p-2 order-2 md:order-1">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
          [a physcial representation of what Big Data Sprawl & Decentralized Ownership.  This image is labeled something like: Big Data Sprawl.  One possible image we could use is a business park with buildings customized to Big Data Players.  In the plaza of the business park, show a bunch of faceless people wheeling and dealing in everyone's data]
          <br><br>
          [Around the image you can have labels with arrows or talk bubbles that read: "-> Data In", "Data Out ->", "LLM", "Forcasting", "DataOps", "DevOps", "Version Control", "Acid Transactions", etc.  The point of these labels are to show 2 things..1) At the end of the day Big Data and vera are doing the same simple things with the same tooling, and 2) We're more nimble and lean then they are]
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Middle -->
      <div class="p-2 order-1 md:order-2">
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center text-gray-900 mb-8">What is <Vera />?</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700"><Vera /> is a Data Engine.  It shrinks down AI, Business Intelligence & Data Management tools so that they can be run locally by anyone.</p>
          <br>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">The Personal Data Computing golden age is here?</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right -->
      <div class="p-2 order-3 md:order-3">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
          [a physcial representation of what vera might look like.  This image is labeled something like: Lean Data Machine.<br><br>Possible idea...a rough drawing of square box that represents a Lakehouse with a rectangle box on top of it that represents AI/GPU]
          <br><br>
          [Around the image you can have labels with arrows or talk bubbles that read: "-> Data In", "Data Out ->", "LLM", "Forcasting", "DataOps", "DevOps", "Version Control", "Acid Transactions", etc.  The point of these labels are to show 2 things..1) At the end of the day Big Data and vera are doing the same simple things with the same tooling, and 2) We're more nimble and lean then they are]
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bg-gray-50 py-24">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-center">
      <div class="p-2 order-1 md:order-1">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center text-gray-900 mb-8">What is <VeraTree />?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8"><VeraTree /> is an extension of <Vera />. It integrates your data into a KnowledgeGraph that sits on top of an already powerful data engine.</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8">If <Vera /> makes your data clean, fresh & AI-ified then <VeraTree />, by mapping it to a global semantic layer, makes your data valuable.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right cell (shows second on mobile, second on desktop) -->
      <div class="p-2 order-2 md:order-2">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
           Possible idea...a rough drawing of square box that represents a Lakehouse with a rectangle box on top of it that represents AI/GPU with a tree growing out of it that represents a miniaturized GraphRag system
          <br><br>
          [Around the image you can have labels with arrows or talk bubbles that read: "-> Data In", "Data Out ->".  Then next to the Lakehouse part have an arrow pointing up that says "Data Quality" and then an arrow going up next to the Tree (Knowledge Graph) that says "Data Value"]
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


